# Protocol architecture

## Layering (strict)

**Controllers → Services → Adapters**

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| Adapters | **Only `services` may import `adapters`.** Controllers and other layers must not. |
| `lib` | Code under `lib` uses **constructor-injected** adapters per `src/lib/protocol/interfaces/*.interface.ts`. **Do not** import adapter implementations in `lib`. |
| Controllers | Import **services** (or graph factories). Handle HTTP only; **no** direct adapter imports. |
| Services | **Must not import other services.** Use **events**, **queues**, or **shared lib/graphs** instead. |

## Adapter pattern

- **Contracts:** `src/lib/protocol/interfaces/` (e.g. `database.interface.ts`).
- **Implementations:** `src/adapters/`. Controllers get abstractions via **constructor injection** (testability).

## Controller routing

Class-based controllers: `@Controller(prefix)`, `@Get` / `@Post`, optional **guards**. Registration via **`RouteRegistry`**; dispatch from **`main.ts`**. See `router.decorators.ts`.

## Template files (read before editing)

- `protocol/src/controllers/controller.template.md`
- `protocol/src/services/service.template.md`
- `protocol/src/queues/queue.template.md`
- `protocol/src/lib/protocol/agents/agent.template.md`
